data.name: label1.Text
data.value:
In a 5-by-5 grid game, the player who is playing "X" always goes first.
Players alternate placing Xs and Os on the board until either player has five in a row, horizontally, vertically, or diagonally.
If a player is able to draw five Xs or five Os in a row, then that player wins.
If all squares are filled and neither player has made a complete row of Xs or Os, then the game is a draw.
